register.name: BT_RX_MEMBER_ADDRESS
register.comment: Specifies possible BR/EDR piconet member addresses (logical transport address, LT_ADDR) to receive on. The value of these in relation to a received packet with a logical transport address (LT_ADDR) in the packet header affects which of the link types from BT_RX_LINK_TYPE to apply when processing the received packet internally in the hardware (see description of BT_RX_LINK_TYPE for details). Bits [6:4]: Secondary Receive Member Address. Can be set to 0 to defeat/ignore, in which case the Secondary Link Type in BT_RX_LINK_TYPE is also ignored. Bits [2:0]: Primary Receive Member Address. If the logical transport address (LT_ADDR) of a received packet is non-zero but doesn't match either of the given member addresses, then a BT_RX_EVENT_TYPE_MEMBER_ERROR is generated instead of a BT_RX_EVENT_TYPE_SUCCESS. If both receive member addresses are set to 0, only broadcast traffic can be received as any received packet with a non-zero logical transport address (LT_ADDR) will result in a BT_RX_EVENT_TYPE_MEMBER_ERROR. Note: if the Primary Link Type specified in BT_RX_LINK_TYPE is BT_LINK_TYPE_SETUP_ID or BT_LINK_TYPE_SETUP_FHS, then the Secondary Receive Member Address given in this register is ignored.
